<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,727,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">
[
<emphasis bold="true" box="[161,339,727,753]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">Author’s Note:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3015251320" collectionCode="CNC, USNM" country="United States of America" county="Cotypes" location="There" municipality="Hull" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" specimenCount="55" specimenCount-female="15" specimenCount-male="14" typeStatus="holotype">
According to Ms Lisa Bartels (
<collectionCode box="[690,753,727,753]" country="Canada" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/y2kv-9w3k" name="Canadian National Collection of Insects, Arachnids, and Nematodes" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">CNC</collectionCode>
), there are 
<specimenCount box="[875,1008,727,754]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">26 syntypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1956" box="[1044,1142,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Bathypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1142,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">B. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
housed in the Hull collection; Hull stated at the end of the published description that there were 
<specimenCount box="[951,1041,763,789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" type="male">14 male</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1096,1208,763,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" type="female">15 female</specimenCount>
cotypes, in addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[222,320,799,825]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[376,469,799,825]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">allotype</typeStatus>
, suggesting the subsequent destruction of three specimens. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:2845F361FFF8F664D5F4FD7D857B40D9:A53314ACFFF8F664D117FCED83AF4061" box="[1140,1205,799,825]" country="United States of America" county="Cotypes" municipality="Hull" name="There" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">There</location>
are no specimens in the 
<collectionCode box="[192,276,835,861]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="14" pageNumber="574" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
, (
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:2845F361FFF8F664D5F4FD7D857B40D9:A53314ACFFF8F664D445FCB186FC4005" box="[294,486,835,861]" country="United States of America" county="Cotypes" municipality="Hull" name="Chris Thompson" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">Chris Thompson</location>
, pers. comm.) despite the fact that 
<collectingMunicipality box="[874,924,835,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">Hull</collectingMunicipality>
clearly stated that “ 
<collectingCounty box="[1144,1239,835,861]" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">Cotypes</collectingCounty>
will be deposited in the 
<collectingCountry box="[221,371,871,897]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="574">United States</collectingCountry>
National Museum.”]
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
